# Commit Convention

All commits MUST follow the Conventional Commits format.

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <short description>

[optional body]
```

## Types

| Type | When to use |
|------|-------------|
| `feat` | New feature or functionality |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `refactor` | Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature |
| `style` | UI/CSS changes, design adjustments |
| `docs` | Documentation changes |
| `test` | Adding or updating tests |
| `chore` | Build process, dependencies, config changes |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |

## Scopes

| Scope | Where |
|-------|-------|
| `frontend` | Changes in `apps/frontend/` |
| `backend` | Changes in `apps/backend/` |
| `auth` | Authentication-related changes |
| `ui` | Component or design system changes |
| `api` | API routes or controllers |
| `db` | Database migrations or models |
| `config` | Configuration files |
| `docs` | Documentation files |

## Rules

- Description must be in **lowercase**
- Description must be in **English**
- Description must use **imperative mood**: "add", "fix", "update" — NOT "added", "fixes", "updating"
- Max 72 characters on the first line
- No period at the end of the description

## Examples

```
feat(auth): add password reset flow
fix(api): return 404 when product not found
refactor(frontend): extract product card into separate component
style(ui): update button hover state to use accent-primary-hover
docs(api): document pagination conventions
test(backend): add functional tests for products endpoint
chore(frontend): add vitest and testing library
feat(db): add products migration
```

## Bad examples (FORBIDDEN)

```
fixed stuff                      ← no type, no scope, past tense
Update component                 ← no type, no scope, capitalized
feat: Added new login page       ← past tense, capitalized, period
WIP                              ← not descriptive
```
